SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 1130
By Hensley
A RESOLUTION to honor and recognize McKinley Sullivan, 2026
Top Ten Senior at Lewis County High School.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should pause to pay
tribute to those students who, through their natural talents and unflagging commitment to
academic excellence, have distinguished themselves in the classroom; and
WHEREAS, McKinley Sullivan is one such exceptional student, who was recently named
a Top Ten Senior of the 2026 graduating class at Lewis County High School; and
WHEREAS, through diligent study, steady composure during examinations, and
steadfast commitment of time and talent, Ms. Sullivan has achieved outstanding academic
success and joined the ranks of the best and brightest students in Tennessee and our country;
and
WHEREAS, in her remarkable high school career, McKinley Sullivan has earned an
exemplary grade point average while participating in numerous extracurricular activities,
including football cheer, Anchor Club, and community service; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Sullivan is the activities director of Beta Club, has received many
classroom awards, and was designated as a Girls State alternate; and
WHEREAS, her favorite pastimes include tanning, shopping, reading, getting her nails
done, and spending time with her family, friends, boyfriend, and boyfriend's family; and
WHEREAS, her display of intellectual aptitude and ambition surely bodes well for her
future success as a student at University of Tennessee at Chattanooga, where she plans to
study physics; and
WHEREAS, McKinley Sullivan's noteworthy achievement is a tremendous source of
pride for her parents, Blake Sullivan and Skyelar Sullivan, her school, and her community; and
SJR1130
017666
- 1 -

WHEREAS, Ms. Sullivan's dedication to excellence is clearly deserving of the respect,
admiration, and commendation of this General Assembly; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we hereby commend and honor McKinley Sullivan
of Lewis County High School on being named a 2026 Top Ten Senior, salute her impressive
academic achievement, and extend to her our best wishes for a happy, successful future.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
